This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques for extracting location names from social media data. The paper uses statistical language models based on gazetteers such as OpenStreetMap, Geonames, and DBpedia. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for identifying location names from unstructured data, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for handling variability in location names, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories. Finally, the paper involves data mining techniques for extracting location names from social media data, which makes cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) a possible category.
